# Project Structure

## Source Layout

```
src/
  Fabrica.Core/         — Shared primitives (collections, memory, threading, jobs)
  Fabrica.Pipeline/     — Producer-consumer pipeline (SPSC queue, loops)
  Fabrica.Engine/       — Simulation engine (world, coordinators)
  Fabrica.ConsoleApp/   — Entry point and console host
tests/
  Fabrica.Core.Tests/
  Fabrica.Pipeline.Tests/
  Fabrica.Engine.Tests/
plans/<date>/           — Design plans and architectural decisions
research/<date>/        — Technical investigations and literature surveys
```

## Architecture

- **Pipeline**: `ProductionLoop` (simulation) and `ConsumptionLoop` (rendering) connected by a
  lock-free SPSC `ProducerConsumerQueue<T>`. Production runs at a fixed timestep; consumption
  runs at variable rate.
- **Threading**: One thread per core, pinned. Coordinators (Thread 0 = sim, Thread 1 = render)
  also participate as workers. Work-stealing deque per worker for job scheduling.
- **Memory**: Object pools with `IAllocator<T>` pattern. Zero GC allocations on hot paths.
  Deferred cleanup via per-thread SPSC log buffers.
- **Determinism**: Simulation is deterministic. Same inputs → same outputs. Time dilation is
  allowed; work-shedding per tick is not.

## Key Design Principles

- Minimize cross-core cache line bouncing. Prefer per-thread data over shared atomics.
- Immutable shared data (Shared cache state on all cores, zero invalidation).
- Batch cross-thread coordination to phase boundaries (fork-join points).
- See `research/2026-04-03/synthesis-and-recommendations.md` for the full rationale.
